      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your car's alternator is the engine's battery charger, constantly pumping electricity back into the system to keep the battery charged and power the car's electrical components while you drive. If your alternator is shot, you'll likely notice the dashboard warning light flashing, dim lights that flicker when you rev the engine, or the engine stalling immediately after turning off the ignition because the battery has drained completely. Since you're experiencing your car dying while driving or right after shutting it off, it's highly probable that your alternator is failing to maintain the necessary voltage, and you should have it inspected by a mechanic soon.\n\n**Note:** While I can explain the mechanics, I cannot physically diagnose your vehicle. If you suspect a mechanical failure, please consult a professional mechanic for a proper diagnosis and repair.",
